    "This detailed search approach was designed to maximize coverage and replicability of the review.",
    "Inclusion and exclusion criteriaWe established the following inclusion and exclusion criteria to ensure a robust review of the literature: Inclusion criteria• Empirical studies that demonstrate AI's impact on higher education and/or sustainability, with a particular focus on practical applications.",
    "• Peer-reviewed articles published in the last ten years, providing contemporary insights.",
    ":(0123456789) Discover Sustainability (2025) 6:23 | https://doi.org/10.1007/s43621-025-00809-6 Review• Full-text articles published in English to maintain accessibility and consistency.",
    "Exclusion criteria• Theoretical studies without empirical evidence or practical application.• Studies that address AI or sustainability independently without linking the two.• Articles lacking discussion on ethical considerations related to AI in higher education.This approach ensures the inclusion of relevant, high-quality studies, mitigating selection bias and maintaining the rigor of the review."
